      "comment": "",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "CommentSubheadingTitle",
          "title": "Samaria's population deported",
          "precomment": "",
          "refgroups": [
            {
              "type": "ReferenceGroup",
              "primaryrefs": [
                {
                  "type": "Reference",
                  "refclass": "A",
                  "comment": "Sargon II of Assyria completed the siege begun by Shalmaneser V, deporting (according to his own annals) over 27,000 of Samaria's inhabitants.",
                  "continuation": false,
                  "bcvreferences": [
                    "12017006-12017018"
                  ],
                  "parallels": []
                }
              ],
              "secondaryrefs": [],
              "seealsos": [
                {
                  "type": "Reference",
                  "refclass": "B",
                  "comment": "",
                  "continuation": false,
                  "bcvreferences": [
                    "12018011-12018012"
                  ],
                  "parallels": []
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "CommentSubheadingTitle",
          "title": "Samaria resettled by other peoples",
          "precomment": "",
          "refgroups": [
            {
              "type": "ReferenceGroup",
              "primaryrefs": [
                {
                  "type": "Reference",
                  "refclass": "A",
                  "comment": "This resettlement, the first of several, led to intermarriage, and is seen by many as the origin of the Samaritans of NT times.",
                  "continuation": false,
                  "bcvreferences": [
                    "12017024"
                  ],
                  "parallels": []
                }
              ],
              "secondaryrefs": [],
              "seealsos": [
                {
                  "type": "Reference",
                  "refclass": "B",
                  "comment": "",
                  "continuation": false,
                  "bcvreferences": [
                    "15004002",
                    "15004009-15004010"
                  ],
                  "parallels": []
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "CommentSubheading",
      "title": "Religion in Samaria after its fall",
      "precomment": "",
      "refgroups": [],
      "comment": "",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "CommentSubheadingTitle",
          "title": "Syncretism arises in Samaria",
          "precomment": "",
          "refgroups": [
            {
              "type": "ReferenceGroup",
              "primaryrefs": [
                {
                  "type": "Reference",
                  "refclass": "A",
                  "comment": "Those resettled brought their own gods with them, but also worshipped the LORD as the god of the land. Ultimately these inter-mixed peoples would abandon their polytheism and would accept the law of Moses.",
                  "continuation": false,
                  "bcvreferences": [
                    "12017025-12017041"
                  ],
                  "parallels": []
                }
              ],
              "secondaryrefs": [],
              "seealsos": []
            }
          ]
        },
        {
